Day 1
-daily_pattern
    -made this function in order to replicate data and output a multiplier number correlated with time of
     day
    -less power is being using around night time and higher around day time as data suggest
     [https://energymag.net/daily-energy-demand-curve/] 
     [https://www.eia.gov/electricity/gridmonitor/dashboard/electric_overview/US48/US48]
    -used sinusodial function in order to create deeps and peaks in the graph to replicate a graph
     found online using real data
    -
-DayOfWeekMultiplier
    -made this function for the purpose of replicating data and output a multiplier number correlated with day of week
    -Used most recent data to support this 
     [https://www.eia.gov/electricity/gridmonitor/dashboard/electric_overview/US48/US48]
    -showed that is was lower on weekends so the multiplier number should be lower
    -
-DayOfYearMultiplier
    -made this function for to replicate data and output a multiplier number correlated with the day of the year
    -most energy is used during the hottest days and coldest days because of AC
    
     

